From e2721bef42eaddd06e74b6caad873fe2fc806223 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: John Vogel <jvogel@stygian.me>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 15:07:10 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Revert "Use console_scripts entry point for pipx compatibility"

The subject commit causes python to not be able to find solaar's files
when it is relocated outside of python's standard sitelib. We need to
install solaar's files as we do because solaar uses a vendored hid_parser
that conflicts with py3-hid-parser. Fedora handles this by removing the
vendored hid_parser; there are many changes to the vendored hid_parser,
so I think that that approach is questionable. This fix is mentioned in
https://github.com/pwr-Solaar/Solaar/issues/3262#issuecomment-4892446084.
While I agree with skitt's appraisal that this may not be the
best fix for the long run, it works and is not invasive.


This reverts commit 8cea17fc46a5e6eb3c19856ec1fcd46ba7f126a0.
---
 setup.py | 6 +-----
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/setup.py b/setup.py
index 41506287..06cc4c17 100755
--- a/setup.py
+++ b/setup.py
@@ -90,9 +90,5 @@ setup(
     packages=find_packages(where="lib"),
     data_files=list(_data_files()),
     include_package_data=True,
-    entry_points={
-        "console_scripts": [
-            "solaar = solaar.gtk:main",
-        ],
-    },
+    scripts=glob("bin/*"),
 )
-- 
2.55.0

